<br>
That being said it seems like Sony prefers the &quot;quick fix&quot; to the real solution.  I think one of the easiest ways for them to address the problem would be to just increase the effect of Hastened Instigation.  I forget what the final recycle time on AE Taunt is supposed to move to with HI 3 (11 minutes?), but it's too long to be used on a regular basis just to grab aggro at the beginning of a fight.  <br>
<br>
If they reduced the final recycle time with HI 3 to around 3 minutes you could use it about once every 2 or 3 fights.  Combined with regular taunt (which does work sometimes) I think that would solve most of our aggro issues.  We'd have access to quick aggro when we need it via AE taunt, but for sustained aggro we'd still be reliant on good weapons.<br>
<br>
I don't know if 3 minutes is the right number, I just threw it out there as something that feels about right to me.  The reason I like this idea is it's the type of thing that Sony might actually implement.  It would be trivial to put in and I don't think anyone could claim it would break anything.  <br>
<br>
Only downside I see is it doesn't help the sub 60 warriors any.  I guess an alternative would be to reduce the base recycle time on AE taunt and leave the HI effects the same.  That would have similar drawbacks but would be available to a larger base of the warrior population sooner.  Anyway wondering what other warriors think. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=472195">Khumak</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
